==English==
===Spellings===
*[[tuwel]] Middle English

===Etymology===
From Old French [[tuel]] ‘tube, pipe’ (French [[tuyau]]), cognate with Spanish and Portuguese [[tudel]], from Proto-Romance.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'tju:əl/

